Daddy Good Deeds is a Hong Kong television comedy serial produced by TVB and featuring Ha Yu, Steven Ma, Linda Chung,Nancy Wu,Edwin Siu, Mak Cheung-ching, Cilla Kung and Chow Chung. Filming and post- production took place in the autumn of 2011 and the premier episode aired on March 19, 2012. The producer was Mui Siu-ching and was her last work for TVB after being with the station for 25 years.

Ko Yi-man (Ha Yu) is the owner of a pawn shop and a devoted father to his son Ko Wai-ting (Mak Cheung-ching) and two daughters Ko Yu-chu (Linda Chung) and Ko Yu-po (Cilla Kung). However unknown to his children one of them is not his biologically but an abandoned child, the symbolic &quot;collateral&quot; in a good luck ritual made many years previously. When the receipt for the tansaction comes to light first speculation about the truth and then the truth itself threatens the destruction of a family that he has given everything for and Gao Yi-wen must fight to keep his family together.
